By that set of requirements(position 4 (P4) = (L,I,M,V,A,G,W,Y,F); P5= G; P6, (I,L,R,S,T,N,D,W,Y); P7=(D,N,S,T); P8= I; P9=(P,K,R,H); P10=(V,T,I,K)),  this peptide sequence was retrieved, and subsequently stated to be recognized by the T cell clone, validating the requirement definition and suggesting that similarity rather than homology is required for Ag recognition.

The phosphatidylinositol mannoside are common to several Mycobaterium species, including the ones tested in this study, M. tuberculosis and M.leprae.
